# Phase 3: Stream Parsers Implementation

## Goal
Implement robust stream parsers for HLS (M3U8), DASH (MPD), and Smooth Streaming (ISM) formats, capable of extracting variants, segments, and encryption keys.

## User Review Required
> [!NOTE]
> This phase introduces new file types support (ISM) and enhances existing parsing logic.

## Proposed Changes

### [Shared Types]

#### [NEW] [stream.ts](file:///home/rob/cat-catch-enhanced/src/shared/types/stream.ts)
- Define interfaces for `MasterPlaylist`, `MediaPlaylist`, [StreamVariant](file:///home/rob/cat-catch-enhanced/src/shared/types/resource.ts#63-75), [Track](file:///home/rob/cat-catch-enhanced/src/shared/types/resource.ts#79-87), [Segment](file:///home/rob/cat-catch-enhanced/src/shared/types/resource.ts#147-156).

### [Parsers]

#### [NEW] [M3U8Parser.ts](file:///home/rob/cat-catch-enhanced/src/background/parsers/M3U8Parser.ts)
- Parse Master Playlists to extract variants (bandwidth, resolution, codecs).
- Parse Media Playlists to extract segments and keys.
- **Enhanced Features**:
  - Handle discontinuities (`#EXT-X-DISCONTINUITY`).
  - Extract encryption keys (`#EXT-X-KEY`).
  - Support `EXT-X-MAP` (init segments).

#### [NEW] [MPDParser.ts](file:///home/rob/cat-catch-enhanced/src/background/parsers/MPDParser.ts)
- Parse DASH manifests (XML).
- Extract AdaptationSets and Representations.
- Support `SegmentTemplate`, `SegmentTimeline`, and `SegmentList`.

#### [NEW] [ISMParser.ts](file:///home/rob/cat-catch-enhanced/src/background/parsers/ISMParser.ts)
- Parse Smooth Streaming manifests (XML).
- Extract Tracks and QualityLevels.
- Generate chunk URLs.

#### [NEW] [ParserFactory.ts](file:///home/rob/cat-catch-enhanced/src/background/parsers/ParserFactory.ts)
- Factory to select the correct parser based on content content/extension.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Build verification.

### Manual Verification
- **HLS**: Load a test `.m3u8` stream. Check if variants are detected.
- **DASH**: Load a test `.mpd` stream. Check if qualities are detected.
- **ISM**: Load a test `.ism` stream. Check if detected.
